Sphinx rstdemo directive extension to display raw reStructuredText and rendered output.

Output Sample
==============
:output: http://packages.python.org/sphinxcontrib.rstdemo/
:source: http://packages.python.org/sphinxcontrib.rstdemo/_sources/index.txt


Features
========
* Provide ``rstdemo`` directive to display raw and rendered reStrucutredText.


Setup
=====
Install sphinxcontrib.rstdemo with easy_install or pip or some installer::

   $ easy_install sphinxcontrib.rstdemo

and add to extension in your conf.py::

   extensions = ['sphinxcontrib.rstdemo']


Using rstdemo directive
========================

You can use as ``code-block:: rst`` directive::

   .. rstdemo::

      Some text line.
      Second line will joined to 1st line.

      * item 1
      * item 2

        * item 2-1
        * item 2-2

      * item 3


Requirements
============
* sphinx 1.0.x or later.


